He didn't repeal Obamacare but he's basically put it on a path to implode and it should implode because it was unconstitutional to begin with.  I can't recall any part of the Constitution stating the American government has the right to force citizens purchase a product or be taxed/penalized if they don't buy said product.  When it comes to the tax cuts, I'll believe it when I see it.  It would be nice to get any type of tax cut but I've heard presidents break promises and lie before so with Trump it won't be anything new.  Dubya said we would be greeted as liberators in Iraq and how'd they work out?  Obama said that if we like our plan, we can keep our plan and if we like our doctor, we can keep our doctor and how'd they work out?  The only way to fix healthcare is to get congress out of bed with the insurance and pharmaceutical companies.  Make it where senators and representatives can't profit off their voting records while in Congress.  Take away any incentives from them and they will have no choice to but finally serve the American people.
